------------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party components
------------------------------------------------------------------------

This repository vendors a patched copy of `libsql` under `vendor/libsql-patched/`
to enable mobile build and runtime compatibility. `libsql` is distributed under
the MIT License. See `vendor/libsql-patched/` for the upstream license and
notice files.

The Napaxi mobile SDK redistributes prebuilt, unmodified third-party native
binaries that provide its on-device Linux sandbox:

- PRoot (`libproot.so`) — GPL-2.0-only.
- Samba talloc (`libtalloc.so.2`) — LGPL-3.0-or-later.
- musl libc loader (`libldmusl.so`) — MIT.
- An Alpine Linux minirootfs image (`alpine-rootfs.bin`) — mixed per-package
  licenses.

On iOS, the SDK statically links the `iSHCore` user-mode Linux emulator
(`iSHCore 0.3.0`), which is GPL-licensed, and ships an Alpine Linux rootfs
archive for the native Swift Package.

These components are governed by their own licenses, not by the Apache-2.0
license of Napaxi itself. Provenance, integrity, and source-code availability
for the bundled binaries are documented in `THIRD-PARTY-LICENSES.md` and
`packages/flutter/android/jniLibs/THIRD-PARTY.md` or
`packages/ios/Vendor/iSHCore/THIRD-PARTY.md`.

Runtime dependencies are declared in `Cargo.toml` and `pubspec.yaml` files
throughout the repository. Each dependency is governed by its own license.
